{
  "skillId": "identify-parts-of-expression",
  "atomType": "R",
  "theory": {
    "intro": "Every algebraic expression is built from **terms**. Each term carries its own sign, and a term with a pronumeral has a **coefficient** (the number multiplying it). A term that is just a number is the **constant term**.",
    "facts": [
      "A **term** is a part of an expression; terms are **separated by addition**.",
      "Treat every subtraction as **adding a negative**, so the sign travels with the term: $3x - 4y$ has terms $3x$ and $-4y$.",
      "The **coefficient** is the number multiplying a pronumeral. In $3x$ it is $3$; in $-9x$ it is $-9$; in $\\frac{x}{3}$ it is $\\frac{1}{3}$.",
      "A term written as just a pronumeral has coefficient $1$: $x$ has coefficient $1$ and $-x$ has coefficient $-1$.",
      "The **constant term** is a term with no pronumeral. If every term has a pronumeral, the constant term is $0$."
    ],
    "steps": [
      "Rewrite subtractions.",
      "Split into terms.",
      "Read coefficient.",
      "Find constant."
    ]
  },
  "practice": {
    "foundation": [
      {
        "q": "List all the terms in $4a + 2b + c$.",
        "a": "$4a,\\ 2b,\\ c$",
        "solution": [
          {
            "math": "$4a + 2b + c$"
          },
          {
            "math": "$4a,\\ 2b,\\ c$",
            "note": "Split into terms"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "q": "State the coefficient of $n$ in $17n + 24$.",
        "a": "$17$",
        "solution": [
          {
            "math": "$17n + 24$"
          },
          {
            "math": "$17$",
            "note": "Read coefficient"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "q": "Identify the constant term in $2x + 3y + 6$.",
        "a": "$6$",
        "solution": [
          {
            "math": "$2x + 3y + 6$"
          },
          {
            "math": "$6$",
            "note": "Find constant"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "q": "State the coefficient of $n$ in $n + 51$.",
        "a": "$1$",
        "solution": [
          {
            "math": "$n + 51$"
          },
          {
            "math": "$= 1n + 51$",
            "note": "Hidden $1$"
          },
          {
            "math": "$1$",
            "note": "Read coefficient"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "q": "State the coefficient of $x$ in $\\frac{x}{3}$.",
        "a": "$\\frac{1}{3}$",
        "solution": [
          {
            "math": "$\\frac{x}{3}$"
          },
          {
            "math": "$= \\frac{1}{3}x$",
            "note": "Rewrite"
          },
          {
            "math": "$\\frac{1}{3}$",
            "note": "Read coefficient"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "development": [
      {
        "q": "List all the terms in $3x - 4y + 9$.",
        "a": "$3x,\\ -4y,\\ 9$",
        "solution": [
          {
            "math": "$3x - 4y + 9$"
          },
          {
            "math": "$= 3x + (-4y) + 9$",
            "note": "Rewrite subtractions"
          },
          {
            "math": "$3x,\\ -4y,\\ 9$",
            "note": "Split into terms"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "q": "State the coefficient of $a$ in $-2a + 4b + 9$.",
        "a": "$-2$",
        "solution": [
          {
            "math": "$-2a + 4b + 9$"
          },
          {
            "math": "$-2$",
            "note": "Read coefficient"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "q": "State the coefficient of $x$ in $18 - 9x$.",
        "a": "$-9$",
        "solution": [
          {
            "math": "$18 - 9x$"
          },
          {
            "math": "$= 18 + (-9x)$",
            "note": "Rewrite subtractions"
          },
          {
            "math": "$-9$",
            "note": "Read coefficient"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "q": "State the coefficient of $x$ in $\\frac{3x}{7}$.",
        "a": "$\\frac{3}{7}$",
        "solution": [
